# 06 | Competitive Landscape

## We Win Where Others Don't Play

| Platform | Vendor Discovery | Booking & Payment | Contact Masking | Two-Sided Marketplace | Event-Specific |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Eventore** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| The Knot / WeddingWire | ✅ | ❌ (off-platform) | ❌ | Partial | Wedding only |
| Thumbtack | Partial | Partial | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| HoneyBook | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ (vendor-side only) | Partial |
| Cvent | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ (enterprise) | ✅ |
| Bark.com | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |

### Our Moat
1. **Only platform** combining discovery + secure messaging + escrow payment in events
2. **Multi-category** — covers venues, caterers, DJs, photographers, decor, anchors
3. **Contact masking** drives all transactions through the platform (no off-platform leakage)
4. **Cultural tags** — unique feature for multicultural weddings (South Asian, Chinese, Caribbean)
5. **Network effects** — more vendors → more planners → more vendors (flywheel)

### Comparable Valuations
- **The Knot Worldwide** — $933M acquisition (2019), ~$450M annual revenue
- **Thumbtack** — $3.2B valuation (2021), ~$400M revenue
- **HoneyBook** — $2.4B valuation (2021), ~$135M ARR
- **Cvent** — $4.6B Blackstone acquisition (2023)

> *Eventore captures the $0–$500K annual spend segment that Cvent ignores and the multi-vendor coordination layer that The Knot doesn't offer.*

